Load 349.82 Hz49.82 HzFalse{(49.82, 3)}

claim.claim-text:
A method of changing power consumption of a portfolio of energy loads (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) connected to an energy distribution grid (112) that each has a power consumption, said method comprising:
receiving, at a central unit (160), a portfolio response function (504) indicating a desired power response of said portfolio of energy loads (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) to a signal able to be measured on said distribution grid (112) at each of said energy loads (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526);
receiving an optimization function having a term indicating for each energy load (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) a probability that said each energy load (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) will have an available power amount at particular signal values;
maximizing said optimization function to produce for said each energy load (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) a local response function indicating a power change amount in response to variations in said signal; and
dispatching said local response functions to their respective energy loads (180, 182, 184, 186; 522-526) from said central unit (160), whereby said portfolio response function (504) is realized by the combined operation of said local response functions.
